Rubisco activity, the key enzyme in photosynthesis, was estimated from the rate of NADH oxidation. Fresh leaf tissue was homogenized in 50 mM phosphate buffer (pH 8.0) and centrifuged to collect the supernatant. The reaction mixture contained 50 mM Tris-HCl buffer (pH 8.0), 2 mM RuBP, 0.3 mM NADH, and enzyme regulators (phosphoglycerate kinase (PGK), phosphoglycerate mutase (PGAM), and glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase (GAPDH)), ATP, MgCl2, and KHCO3. A small volume of the enzyme extract was added to initiate the reaction. The reduction in NADH absorbance was tested at 340 nm. Rubisco activity was calculated as54,55:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
